Citation.sTitle: Refractive Indices and Molar Refractivities of Molten Rare-Earth Trichlorides and Their Mixtures with Alkali Chlorides
Citation.sAbstract: New experimental data on the refractive indices and molar refractivities of molten cerium, neodymium, samarium, and gadolinium trichlorides and CeCl3 ACl, SmCl3 ACl, Gd3Cl ACl (A = Na, 0.5Na 0.5K, K, and Cs) mixtures depending on the temperature and composition are reported. It is shown that the relative deviations of the molar refractivity of mixtures from their magnitudes inherent to the hypothetic ideal solutions increase as radii of alkali metal cations rises. The difference in variation of the Ln3+-ions electron polarizability with the atomic number or ionic radius is revealed for cerium and yttrium subgroups of the lanthanide row.

trichlorides, alkali chlorides, molten salt mixtures
